 single continuous path, and without an unshaded neighbor, `r2c6` is isolated.\n\n---\n\n**Conclusion: r2c6 must be shaded**\n\nSince assuming `r2c6` is unshaded leads to a violation of the **Connectivity Rule**, we conclude that our initial assumption was incorrect. Therefore, `r2c6` must be shaded to maintain compliance with all Hitori rules.\n\n---\n\nThis step-by-step approach ensures that we follow the logical deductions required by the rules while avoiding contradictions.",
